The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Blatter likely to be state guest

OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

New Delhi: On April 15, Bengali New Years day, Calcutta football will have one of its honoured guests in Sepp Blatter. 

The Fifa president, who is likely to arrive in the Mecca of Indian football in his private jet early in the morning on Poila Baisakh, is likely to be given the status of a state guest by the West Bengal government. 

According to AIFF sources, president Priyaranjan Das Munshi has already requested the government of West Bengal to declare the Fifa boss as the state guest. 

Blatter would be in Calcutta only for a day and would leave for Delhi the next morning. Elaborate arrangements would be made to welcome the Fifa boss during his journey from the airport to a hotel in Calcutta. 




